Flimsy

Target IP: 192.168.170.220

Scanning



There are five TCP ports open on the target machine. The web applications on port 80 and 43500 look interesting.

Enumeration

Port 43500: HTTP

After enumerating the different ports, I did not find anything useful. The page above is returned for this port. From the nmap scan, I found it is using APISIX/2.8. This application is vulnerable to RCE.

Exploitation


Doing a Google search shows the exploit above can be used against this target. I created a copy of this exploit on my machine.


After launching the exploit against the machine, I gained a shell as the user franklin on port 80.

Privilege Escalation



The cronjob apt-get update is interesting. I Googled and found an article that showed how to escalate privileges using this. The article mentioned apt.conf.d is required with write privileges.



Then I created a reverse shell script inside the directory apt.conf.d. After some time, I gained a reverse shell connection as the user root.
